               <head>Valiullah’s Musaffa</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kitāb al-muṣaffá by Walī Allāh al-Dihlawī, 1702 or 1703-1762 or 1763 </summary>
                  <msItem class="https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104665 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008104963" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_65B-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658651.0x000001 viaf_71535292">Walī Allāh al-Dihlawī, 1702 or 1703-1762 or 1763 </persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658651.0x000001 viaf_71535292">قطب الدّين احمد ابن عبد الرّحيم العمرى الدّهلوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21780">Kitāb al-muṣaffá</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21780">كتاب المصفّىٰ</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on comparative Sunnī jurisprudence, based on the Kitāb-i muvaṭṭā of Mālik ibn Anas, praised as the best in matters of fiqh
</p>
                        <p>Note dated, antedates marginal notes
</p>
                        <p>Notes and recitation notes on margins and flyleaves (by one Shaykh Muḥammad ʿĀshiq) dated 1177/1763-4 (sic, read 1188/1774-5), including a circular table calibrating astrological, banglah calendrical, and directional systems
</p>
                        <p>Seal impression at beginning and end dated 1188/1774-5 </p>
                        <p>Unbound; torn, wormholes, brittle paper; fragile
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
